section_summary: The text appears to be a transcript of a speech given by Dr. Mubarak Al-Tasha during a parliamentary session. He expresses gratitude for the trust placed in him by his fellow members of parliament and hopes to live up to their expectations. He emphasizes the importance of the current stage in Kuwait's history and the responsibilities of the government and parliament in meeting the aspirations of the Kuwaiti people. He also mentions the need for cooperation and collaboration between the government and parliament to achieve these goals. The text also includes references to the agenda of the parliamentary session and the legislative period in which it took place.
